Introduction¶

In this study, I downloaded the data "tmdb-movies.csv" that contains of the movies info such as cast, name, companies name, revenue, budget etc. my aim is to find some statistics such as number of movies in certain years, total revenues and budget, the relation ships between popularity, vote ratings and revenue. All finding will be entitled as a question in head,ng format.

Data Wrangling¶

In this section, I removed duplicate rows and cahnged the rows containing 0 value in attributes budget and revenue with a mean value to protect other attributes' information.Moreover, for each question data is arranged for the investigation.

what is the top 10 years containing the highest number of movies¶

in this question, I listed the movies and created the chart about it. the explanation about the caht will be in the cell under the chart

In [314]:
result=removerevenueZero.groupby("release_year").size().nlargest(10).reset_index().rename(columns={0:"counts"})

resultTopMovie=removerevenueZero.groupby(["release_year"])["id"].apply(list).reset_index()

result=result.sort_values("counts")

newDataFrameMovieForChartName=pd.DataFrame(columns = ['release_year', 'id',"vote_average","original_title"])

for i in range(int(resultTopMovie.shape[0])):
    listOfid=resultTopMovie.iloc[i]["id"]
    maxVal=0
    for j in range(len(listOfid)):
        row=removerevenueZero[removerevenueZero["id"]==listOfid[j]]
        if maxVal <= row["vote_average"].values[0]:
            maxVal=row["vote_average"].values[0]
            rowTemp=row
    newDataFrameMovieForChartName=newDataFrameMovieForChartName.append({'release_year': rowTemp["release_year"].values[0]
                                         ,"id":rowTemp["id"].values[0]
                                          ,"vote_average":rowTemp["vote_average"].values[0]
                                        ,"original_title":rowTemp["original_title"].values[0]}
                                         , ignore_index=True)
    
    

result_all_year=result.set_index('release_year').join(newDataFrameMovieForChartName.set_index('release_year'))
display(result_all_year.head(30))

    ax.annotate(int(p.get_height()),

plt.show()

for i in range(int(resultTopMovie.shape[0])):
    listOfid=resultTopMovie.iloc[i]["id"]
    maxVal=0

        row=removerevenueZero[removerevenueZero["id"]==listOfid[j]]

result=newMovieWithRowOfgenres1.groupby(["release_year","genres"]).size().reset_index().rename(columns={0:"counts"})

topGenreEachYear=pd.DataFrame(columns=["release_year","topGenre","numberOfGenre"])
minVal=result["release_year"].min()
maxVal=result["release_year"].max()+1
for i in range(minVal,maxVal):
    resultSub=result.query(f"release_year == {i}")
    rowTemp=resultSub.loc[resultSub['counts'].idxmax()]
    topGenreEachYear=topGenreEachYear.append({"release_year":rowTemp["release_year"],
                                             "topGenre":rowTemp["genres"],
                                             "numberOfGenre":rowTemp["counts"]},ignore_index=True)

display(topGenreEachYear.head())

            xytext=(5, 0), textcoords='offset points', ha="left", va="center",color="white")
    indexOfYear+=1

ax.set_xlabel("number of genre",fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylabel("year",fontsize=14)
ax.axes.set_title("top genres in each year(1995-2015)",fontsize=16)
plt.show()
